HEADWORD: Retractile
<hw>Re*tract"ile</hw> <pr>(r⟦esl⟧*tr⟦amac⟧kt"⟦icr⟧l)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos>
<ety>[Cf. F. <ets>-r⟦eacute⟧tractile</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Physiol.)</fld>
<def>Capable of retraction; capable of being drawn back or up; <as>as,
the claws of a cat are <ex>retractile</ex></as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Retraction</ent>⟦br⟧
